-- Control: a leading comment (standalone) plus a decl-trailing comment (on the
-- decl's last line) carry NO interior comment, so the decl still reformats
-- normally — the over-wide arg list wraps and the trailing comment stays inline.
wideCall aaaaaaaaaa bbbbbbbbbb cccccccccc dddddddddd =
  someFunction aaaaaaaaaa bbbbbbbbbb cccccccccc dddddddddd  -- trailing
